Zimbabwe’s Annual Inflation Rate Increases to 3.5% in August, Agency Says

-- B y   G o d f r e y   M a r a w a n y i k a
-- 
2011-09-15T07:15:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-15/zimbabwe-inflation-rate-increases-to-3-5-in-august-agency-says.html
Zimbabwe ’s inflation accelerated to
3.5 percent in August from a year earlier, the country’s
statistics office said.  The inflation rate rose from 3.3 percent in July, the
Harare-based National Statistics Agency said in a statement
handed to reporters today.  Prices rose 0.1 percent in the month, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Godfrey Marawanyika in Johannesburg at 
